<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2009/05/07/springsource-tool-suite-now-free">SpringSource Tool Suite now free</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/aa61393fa6484a17e0ed0ca8a533d501?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Christian Dupuis</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2009-05-07 15:57:00.0">May 7, 2009</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="231" href="/blog/2009/05/07/springsource-tool-suite-now-free#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>It was April 27th around 2:39pm, when Rod announced in his <a href="http://europe.springone.com/europe-2009">SpringOne Europe</a> opening keynote:<br></p>
<center>
<strong>“STS will be free!"</strong>
</center>
<p></p>
<p><a href="http://www.namics.com/ueber-uns/namics-team/mitarbeiter/liste/Reto_Meier">Reto Meier</a>, with our partner <a href="http://www.namics.com">namics</a>, took a picture as proof of that very moment and published it on <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/rmz-web/3484819062/">flickr.com</a>. Also the audience at SpringOne seemed to be enthusiastic about the announcement and as a consequence the word was spread to outside of the conference soon after.</p>
<p>So here we are, since Rod promised it, we can’t get out of itâ¦ ;-)</p>
<p style="text-align: center"><a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/rmz-web/3484819062"><img style="margin: 15px; padding: 4px; border: 1px solid #ccc;" src="http://blog.springsource.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/3484819062_5eeba30549.jpg" alt="Rod @ SpringOne" title="Rod @ SpringOne" width="500" height="200" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1866"></a></p>
<p>Today we are proud to deliver on Rod's promise and can announce that the first free versions of STS have been published and can be downloaded from the <a href="http://www.springsource.com/products/sts">product page</a>.</p>
</div>
</section>
